in your home directory

git clone git@github.com:bretweinraub/bash_profiles.git
cd bash_profiles
./install.sh -p bdw # that my profile world
cd ..
ls -l .profile .emacs .emacs_bash

############

The net effect of this is your .profile and .emacs are symlinked to the checked out version.

To create a new "profile" suite, create a new directory in the toplevel of bash_profiles.

